"Lately in my class, my so-called friends make fun of me in private group chats. Part of me wants to report the bullying to adults, but another part is scared that doing so will only make people target me even more. I feel trapped because staying silent doesn’t seem to help either.",TECHNOLOGY,EMOTIONAL,EMOTIONAL,true
"Since changing schools, a group of students has been constantly mocking the way I speak and act. Even after coming home from school, I can’t stop replaying everything in my head. I keep thinking about the jokes, comments, and rumors, and it’s becoming difficult to relax or focus on anything else anymore.",TECHNOLOGY,BULLYING,BULLYING,true
"Lately in my class, someone made a fake account pretending to be me online. I’ve noticed the bullying is starting to affect my sleep, concentration, and motivation. Things I once enjoyed now feel stressful because I constantly worry about being judged or laughed at by others.",TECHNOLOGY,BULLYING,BULLYING,true
"Lately in my class, someone made a fake account pretending to be me online. What hurts the most is that some of the people involved used to act friendly toward me before joining the bullying. Because of this, I’ve started struggling to trust people and often wonder if others secretly dislike me too.",TECHNOLOGY,BULLYING,BULLYING,true
"Since joining sports practice, my teammates blame me whenever something goes wrong. At first I thought ignoring the situation would make it stop, but over time the comments became more personal and emotionally exhausting. Now I feel nervous every morning before school because I constantly expect someone to embarrass me again.",TECHNOLOGY,DANGEROUS,DANGEROUS,true
"For the past several weeks, students constantly criticize my clothes and personal style. The worst part is how quickly rumors and jokes spread online. Even small embarrassing moments suddenly become group chat discussions and social media jokes that follow me everywhere.",TECHNOLOGY,BULLYING,BULLYING,true
